TopicTitle: [ERR] Trying to reload asset from disk that is not stored on disk

Articles.Content:
So I'm getting this as spam in my KSP.log, and I have a fair number of mods. It's not really clear from this what's going on, or even if I should be concerned. Any ideas?

 

[ERR 09:05:25.573] Trying to reload asset from disk that is not stored on disk

[ERR 09:05:34.773] The AssetBundle 'file://C:\GOG Games\Kerbal Space Program_1.1\GameData\GCMonitor\gcmonitor.ksp' can't be loaded because another AssetBundle with the same files are already loaded

[ERR 09:05:34.774] AssetLoader: Bundle is null

Leaving this here for anyone who might run into the same issue.
